MCQ - Font size
The following HTML code is trying to change the fontsize of the paragraph text, but fails to do so.
Why?

<p fontsize='16px';>Why am I wrong?</p>

Select one of the following options.

1)Font size cannot be 16 px. It needs to be 16.
2)The value of fontsize should be 'Arial' or 'Times New Roman'
3) The font-size attribute is incorrect. 
   The correct syntax is <p style = 'font-size: 16px;'>Why am I wrong?</p>
